column1: #Text=is a city in the Prairies and Lakes region of Texas .
#Text=With a population of approximately 661,000 , it is Texas ' 5th largest city .
#Text=It is part of the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex , which has a population exceeding 6 million .
#Text=Sometimes referred to as Cowtown , it is by far closer to its cowboy roots than neighboring Dallas .
#Text=Fort Worth grew from a military camp established at the close of the Mexican War by Gen. Winfield Scott , and named for Gen. William Jenkins Worth who fought in the war .
#Text=Forty-two men of Company F , 2nd Dragoons , established the camp on June 6 , 1849 .
#Text=The Fort Worth to Yuma , Arizona , stage line was established in 1850 .
#Text=The city became the seat of Tarrant County 1860 , and after the Civil War , it became a major shipping and supply depot for cattlemen .
#Text=Fort Worth is located in the American South , and has a subtropical climate with mild winters , hot summers , and a wet spring and fall in between .
#Text=In winter and summer it can also be a very dry place , as it receives warmer , drier weather from the Mojave Desert in the west and the Great Plains in the north .
#Text=Winters are generally mild , with average highs in the mid to upper 50s ( 10-15 °C ) and average lows around the freezing mark ( 0-5 °C ) .
#Text=It is not uncommon for Winter days with highs in the upper 60s ( ~20°C ) with the following days high temperature 20-30 degrees cooler .

#Text=It may snow in Fort Worth a couple times a year , and occasionally winter temperatures will not get above freezing ( 32°F , 0 °C ) , but for the most part winter is just relatively dry and cool .
#Text=There is , however , the danger of freezing rain and ice storms .
#Text=Spring and fall bring very pleasant temperatures , but spring is also known for its storms .
#Text=Fort Worth is at the Southern tip of Tornado Alley , and springtime weather can be quite volatile and severe storms often occur .
#Text=Summers are hot and dry - but often humid - with temperatures frequently surpassing 100 °F ( 38 °C ) .
#Text=Average precipitation in Fort Worth is 33 inches ( 830 mm ) per year .
#Text=The TCU area is dominated by the campus .
#Text=Some unique restaurants and boutiques are mixed with standard college fare , but the campus is beautiful and shows up in force ( and in Purple ) for gamedays
#Text=Square is a city park in downtown that plays host to multiple events year round .
#Text=Night and weekend parking is free and additional security patrols not only keep the area safe , but also can help you find your next destination .
#Text=A national historic district , the Stockyards is the iconic background for which Fort Worth is known .
#Text=The backdrop is all things western from cattle drives and BBQ to country music and belt buckles .
#Text=No trip to Fort Worth is complete without a quick stop here .
#Text=Home to world class museum , the stock show & rodeo as well as numerous restaurants and merchants , this area hosts many of Fort Worth 's main attractions .
#Text=Located across the Trinity River , 2 miles west of downtown , this area could be though of as uptown .
#Text=The area is also known as West 7th .
#Text=Also called South Main and Magnolia , this is the area where artists and more liberal mindsets are welcome .
#Text=The area hosts multiple of the cities micro breweries , bars and restaurants .
#Text=The area is undergoing a renaissance with new building and merchants , but the growth is keeping with the vibe of the current culture .
#Text=While not a single neighborhood , Southwest Fort Worth has a collection of different shopping areas and neighborhood restaurant clusters .
#Text=All the major American carriers and many international ones provide scheduled passenger service into the ( DFW ) , located from downtown Fort Worth .
#Text=This airport is one of three major hubs for American Airlines .
#Text=American Airlines is also headquartered in Fort Worth .

#Text=St is the central hub for Amtrak inter-city trains and Trinity Railway Express ( TRE ) commuter trains to Dallas , along with Greyhound inter-city bus service and local bus service provided by the T. TRE trains can provide a stress-free way to travel between the two cities during rush hour and also serve the more historic at 1600
#Text=Throckmorton St on the south side of downtown .
#Text=Eagle provides daily service between Chicago , Illinois and San Antonio , Texas with stops in Fort Worth and Dallas .
#Text=Also , Amtrak 's Heartland Flyer provides daily service between Fort Worth and Oklahoma City , and points in between .
#Text=Woefully underfunded , passenger train service in the United States is a slow but scenic way to travel , if you are n't too concerned about arriving on time .
#Text=Alternatively , arrive from DFW Airport on TEXRail , another commuter train that provides direct rail service from the airport to downtown Fort Worth .
#Text=Fort Worth may be easily reached via I-20 or I-30 from the east or west , or by I-35W from the north or south .
#Text=I-35 splits into two branches north of the Dallas/Fort Worth metropolitan area , the west branch going to Fort Worth and the east branch ( I-35E ) to Dallas .
#Text=Bus stop is at the Fort Worth Intermodal Transportation Center .
#Text=Also , subsidiaries of Greyhound , such as TNM&O serve as the regional carrier .
#Text=Service from Houston , San Antonio , Austin , Memphis , Little Rock , Oklahoma City , and Norman .
